<ab><lb n="1"/> <w lemma="ὁ">ἡ</w> <w lemma="σορός">σορός</w> <w lemma="εἴμι">ἐσστιν</w> <lb n="2"/> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w> <w lemma="τόπος">τόπος</w> <lb n="3"/> <w lemma="ἐν">ἐν</w> <w>ᾧ</w> <w lemma="ἐπίκειμαι">ἐπίκειτε</w> <lb n="4"/> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Μᾶρκος"><expan><abbr>Μάρ</abbr><ex>κου</ex></expan></name> <name nymRef="#Αὐρήλιος"><expan><abbr>Αὐ</abbr><ex>ρηλίου</ex></expan></name> <name nymRef="#Παπίας">Παπίου</name> <lb n="5"/> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Μελίτων">Μελί<lb n="6" break="no"/>τωνος</name></persName></persName></ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>The sarcophagus and the plot on which it stands belong to Marcus Aurelius Papias, also called Meliton.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The owner is otherwise unknown. The unusual abbreviation of his nomen, like the shortness of the text, could suggest a later date.</p>
         </div>
